# Rootwork Base Rules

## Writing Rules

WRITING RULES — APPLY TO ALL GENERATED CONTENT INCLUDING UI COPY:
- Never use em dashes (—) anywhere. Not in component text, not in comments, not in placeholder copy.
- Never use the pattern "X — Y" or "X - Y" to contrast two ideas.
- Use a period, comma, or restructure the sentence instead.
- This applies to every string, label, heading, body text, and placeholder in every component.
